    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "When attempting to creating a size `0` buffer, Cython throws an exception instead of letting it proceed. To illustrate please see the code below:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ncpdef func():\r\n    cdef const char* p = b\"\"\r\n    cdef const char[::1] mv = <const char[:0:1]>p\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis compiles without issues. However at runtime we get the following exception:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n<some SO file> in View.MemoryView.array.__cinit__()\r\n\r\nValueError: Invalid shape in axis 0: 0.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThough if we assigned an empty `bytes` object to a memory view (also length `0`), this problem would not arise.\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ncpdef func():\r\n    cdef const unsigned char[::1] mv = b\"\"\r\n```",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "FWIW it seems this problem can be worked around by merely increasing the size beforehand and then trimming it after like so\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ncpdef func():\r\n    cdef const char* p = b\"\"\r\n    cdef const char[::1] mv = <const char[:1:1]>p\r\n    mv = mv[:1]\r\n```",
